fields.description:
Roll each tortilla and grill in a panini press for 2-3 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Note: If you don’t have a panini press, place the wrap in a dry pan over medium heat and cook for approximately 2 minutes per side.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To make each panini, spread ½ tbsp. of mustard on the tortilla, followed by 2 slices of deli ham, 1 slice of Swiss cheese, ¼ cup pulled pork, and 2-3 slices of pickle.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large sauté pan over medium heat, warm oil. Add quinoa, buckwheat, and kale, tossing gently. Continue to cook until the kale is slightly wilted and the grains are warm. Add egg whites, blueberries and feta, and continue cooking for 2-3 minutes. Remove from heat for assembly.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: To assemble: Warm the tortillas by heating in a sauté pan over medium-low heat, or place into a storage bag with a damp paper towel and microwave for 20-30 seconds. In each tortilla scoop approximately 1 ¼ cups mixture in the across the middle of the tortilla. Roll like a burrito, leaving one end open. Repeat for remaining tortillas. Serve.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large sauté pan over medium heat, warm oil. Add butternut squash and beans. Sauté until warmed through. Reserve warm for assembly.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Warm the tortillas by heating in a skillet over medium-low heat, or place into a storage bag with a damp paper towel and microwave for 20-30 seconds. In each tortilla place ¾ cup bean and squash mixture and top with 2 tbsp. salsa verde, and 1 tbsp. queso fresco. Repeat for remaining tortillas. Serve.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a crock pot, combine tamari sauce, orange juice, chili-garlic pepper sauce, ginger, five-spice powder, and beef stock. Mix well to combine.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a sauté pan, over medium-high heat, sear all the sides of the pork shoulder to caramelize the outside. Place seared shoulder in crock pot and cook on high for 5-6 hours, or low for 8-9 hours, or until fork tender.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Remove tender pork shoulder from the crock pot and allow to rest for 15 minutes on a plate. Reserve ½ cup liquid from crock-pot. Using a fork, shred the pork into desired sized pieces. Pour reserved liquid over shredded pork. Hold warm for assembly.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: To assemble: Warm the tortillas by heating in a sauté pan over medium-low heat, or place into a storage bag with a damp paper towel and microwave for 20-30 seconds. Place ½ cup prepared Asian slaw into each warmed tortilla. Top the slaw with ½ cup pulled pork, and squeeze one orange wedge over the meat. Repeat for each tortilla shell. Serve.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To assemble: Warm the tortillas by heating in a sauté pan over medium-low heat, or place into a storage bag with a damp paper towel and microwave for 20-30 seconds.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In each tortilla place ½ cup steak and top with ½ cup scrambled eggs, ¼ cup hashbrowns, 2 tbsp. cheese, and 1 tbsp. salsa. Roll like a burrito, leaving one end open. Repeat for remaining tortillas. Serve.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Pre-heat a sauté pan over medium heat.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: To assemble each quesadilla: spread 2 tbsp. spinach artichoke dip on one half of the tortilla, top with ¼ cup chopped shrimp, and ¼ cup shredded mozzarella cheese. Fold the other side of the tortilla over, making a quesadilla. Brown the quesadilla on both sides in the pre-heated sauté pan. Cut into thirds and serve with chunky salsa.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Pre-heat a conventional oven to 350°F.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Place 4 tortillas on a cookie sheet and bake for 10-12 minutes, or until crisp, flipping over half way through cooking.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Meanwhile, smash white beans with a potato smasher, and combine with olive oil, adjust oil to desired creaminess of the beans. Warm the smashed beans in a pre-heated sauté pan, over medium heat. Reserve warm.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Once the tortillas are crisp, on each tortilla spread 3 tbsp. of white beans over the crisp tortilla, sprinkle with ¼ cup ground turkey, ½ cup romaine lettuce, 2 tbsp. queso fresco, 1 tbsp. yellow corn, 1 tbsp. red onion, and sprinkle with cilantro.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: To serve: serve each tostada with a lime wedge to be squeezed over.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Pre-heat conventional oven to 350°F.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Lay each tortilla on a cookie sheet, and brush each side lightly with olive oil. On each tortilla place 1/3 cup pinto beans, 3 tbsp. salsa verde and ¼ cup cheddar cheese. Place into pre-heated oven and bake for 10-15 minutes, or until the tortilla is crispy and the cheese is melted.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Meanwhile, in a skillet over medium heat, warm some olive oil and cook 4 eggs to soft-fried, or desired doneness.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Combine onions, lime juice and olive oil in a bowl. Refrigerate for assembly.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Remove the rancheros from the oven and top each with one egg, ¼ cup shredded lettuce and 2 tbsp. dressed onions. Serve.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Pre-heat a conventional oven to 350°F.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a large sauté pan, over medium heat, add chicken, water and chipotle seasoning. Mix well to combine, and heat until chicken has reached an internal temperature of 165°F on a thermometer.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Warm the tortillas by heating in a skillet over medium-low heat, or place into a storage bag with a damp paper towel and microwave for 20-30 seconds.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: On each tortilla, spread 1 tbsp. sour cream down the middle of the tortilla, then sprinkle with 1 tbsp. shredded cheese, 1 tbsp. diced onions, and ¼ cup chicken. Roll each tortilla so both ends are still open and place them, seam side down in a greased baking dish. Repeat for remaining tortillas, lining them side by side in the baking dish.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Spread 1 cup salsa over the top of the enchiladas and sprinkle remaining ½ cup of cheese over the entire dish. Cover the pan with aluminum foil and bake for 20-25 minutes, or until heated through and the cheese is melted. Serve.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Pre-heat a conventional oven to 400°F. Place a cookie sheet upside down in the oven on a rack.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: On each tortilla, spread 1 tbsp. herb cream cheese. Top each tortilla with 2 tbsp. chicken sausage, 2 tbsp. egg whites, 3 tbsp. shredded cheese, and 1 tbsp. green onion.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Carefully place the pizzas on the hot cookie sheet in the oven. Bake for 12-15 minutes or until the tortilla is crisp and the cheese is melted.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: To serve: cut each tortilla into fourths and sprinkle with cilantro. Serve.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Pre-heat a conventional oven to 350°F.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Warm the tortillas by heating in a sauté over medium-low heat, or place into a storage bag with a damp paper towel and microwave for 20-30 seconds. In the center of each tortilla, spread ¼ cup sauced pulled pork and 1 tbsp. bacon.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Fold the bottom of the tortilla up over the pulled pork, pull down and roll until almost closed. Using the lightly beaten egg, brush a little egg over the edge, and finish rolling to seal. Place seam side down on a parchment lined cookie sheet. Repeat for the remaining tortillas. Using remaining beaten egg, brush each taquito with egg wash to coat the outside to give it a golden brown color for the finished taquitos.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Bake in the pre-heated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F on a thermometer. To serve: place two taquitos on a plate with 2 tbsp. salsa.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Preheat broiler.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: On a baking sheet, combine corn, jalapenos, green chiles, oil, and salt. Broil until corn is lightly browned, 8-10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 425℉.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: In a medium bowl combine 1 cup Pepper Jack, mayonnaise, and sour cream. Stir in corn mixture and transfer to a small baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Pepper Jack.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Return to oven until cheese is melted and dip is bubbly, about 10 minutes.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Sprinkle with green onion and serve with tortilla chips.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a medium bowl combine tomato, bell peppers, onion, cilantro, garlic, serrano, lime juice, olive oil, and salt.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Let sit 5 minutes, then taste and add more lime juice and/or salt if needed.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Serve with tortilla chips.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Mix chips, almonds and 1/3 cup flour in bowl.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Place each chop in flour, pass through egg and place into chip mixture pressing so mixture sticks. Repeat with each pork chop.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Preheat oven to 350°F.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Heat oil in large non-stick skillet over medium heat. Place all pork chops cooking 3 minutes per side, making sure almonds do not burn. Place in oven and cook for about 10 to 12 minutes depending on pork thickness or until no longer pink in the center.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat 1 teaspoon oil in medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add garlic stirring constantly and cook for about 1 minute. Remove from heat into a small mixing bowl. Add yogurt, lemon juice, and chipotle adobo and salt. Mix well until smooth.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat remaining 3 teaspoons oil in medium non-stick skillet. Add onions and cook for 1 minute or until vegetables are tender; stirring frequently. Stir in ground beef. Cook beef for 4 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink; stirring frequently. Drain excess liquid.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: To serve place chips on a platter. Place ground beef on top and sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Drizzle with half of the yogurt sauce. Serve with the rest of the sauce on the side.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat oil in large non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add onions and cook until tender (1-2 minutes); stirring constantly. Stir in ground beef. Cook beef for 4 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink; stirring frequently. Drain excess liquid. Add tomatoes, olives, and ground pepper. Cook until juice from tomatoes has evaporated (about 5 to 7 minutes). Serve on plater. Sprinkle with cheese.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Serve on platter with chips around the edges.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Prepare guacamole by placing the avocados in a bowl and mashing them with a fork. Stir in in tomato, onion, serrano pepper, cilantro, lime juice, tequila, salt, and pepper. Mix well.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat butter in 2-quart non-stick sauce pan over medium heat. Add flour, stir constantly with wire whisk until mixture becomes pasty. Add butter and milk and stir well until the mixture starts thickening, about 2 to 3 minutes; stirring constantly to prevent flour from lumping. Add cheese and stir until cheese melts, about 1 to 2 minutes; stirring constantly.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Lay out chips on a platter and serve cheese sauce on top and guacamole on the side.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add chorizo to skillet (no need to add oil), and cook until crisp, stirring occasionally; set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in same skillet. Add onions and jalapeno and sauté until tender, about 2 minutes; stirring constantly. Add refried black beans and stir to mix. Add cream cheese. Stir well until bean mix is well incorporated and smooth. If needed add 2 tablespoons reduced sodium chicken broth or water; stir occasionally. Heat until beans are heated through, about 4 to 5 minutes.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Place bean mix in platter. Garnish with dollops of sour cream, crumbled Cotija cheese, avocado. Serve with multigrain chips placed around the dip.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat grill to medium high heat.  Brush chicken breasts with olive oil; sprinkle seasoning over both sides of chicken breast.  Place chicken breasts on grill and cook for 5 minutes; turn over, continue cooking for 3 to 4 minutes or until chicken reaches 165 F.  Slice chicken into thin slices; set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description:
To assemble tortilla:  Down center of one corn tortilla place ¼ cup rice, 2 tablespoons black beans, about 2 ½ ounces chicken slices, 2 tablespoons cheese, about 1 tablespoon salsa, about 1 tablespoon guacamole, and about 1 tablespoon sour cream. Roll up or fold in half to serve. 

Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In small bowl mix together shredded chicken and pesto sauce.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description:
To assemble taco: Spread about 2 teaspoons Ranch dressing on one flour tortilla, then down center place about ½ cup shredded chicken, and ¼ cup shredded cheese. Roll up or fold in half to serve.   

Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: If desired, tortilla can be folded in half, placed on medium high hot skillet, then cover and cook first side for 40 seconds; turn over tortilla and cook second side for additional 30 seconds. Remove from heat and cut in half.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Lightly brush one side of a tortilla with canola oil and lay it brushed side down in the skillet. Layer sliced turkey, apple slices, and 1 to 2 tablespoons shredded cheddar cheese across tortilla and cook over medium-high heat.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Place second tortilla on top, brush lightly with oil

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Cook for 3 minutes or until cheese begins to melt. Carefully turn the quesadilla over and cook for 3 more minutes until quesadilla is light golden brown on both sides. Repeat with remaining tortillas.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Cut quesadilla into 4 triangles. Serve warm with a dollop of sour cream, if desired

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In medium skillet, over medium heat, heat olive oil. Add garlic, onion, and peppers.  Cook, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender (3 to 4 minutes).

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Add eggs, salt and pepper; continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until eggs are nearly done (3 to 4 minutes).

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Add cubed cream cheese; continue cooking, stirring gently, until cream cheese begins to melt (1 minute).  Remove from heat.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description:
To assemble burrito: place about ¼ of egg mixture down center of one corn tortilla; roll up and serve immediately.   

Repeat with remaining ingredients and tortillas.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To grill chicken: Preheat oven to 350°F. Brush grilling skillet lightly with 1 teaspoon canola oil in medium high heat. Grill chicken breast for about 5 minutes per side.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Place in pre-heated oven for about 10 to 14 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink. Remove from grilling skillet and let chicken rest for 10 minutes. Shred chicken into small pieces.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Mix pasilla chile salsa, chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup, sour cream, mayonnaise, balsamic vinegar, sugar, and salt in a bowl. Place cooked, shredded chicken into mixture and gently mix until evenly coated.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Heat 1 teaspoon canola oil over medium-high heat in medium non-stick skillet. Add the chicken and pasilla mixture, and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until evenly heated. Divide mixture into 4 portions.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan. Assemble the tacos by filling the tortillas with chicken pasilla mixture. Top with red cabbage and crumbled queso fresco and cilantro.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Make chipotle chimichurri sauce by placing cilantro, parsley, red pepper flakes, kosher salt, 2 tbsp olive oil, white vinegar, chipotle in adobo, onion, and lime juice in food processor and process until smooth.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Season the steak with salt on both sides. Heat 1 tbsp olive oil over medium-high heat in medium non-stick skillet. Add the flank steak and cook as desired (about 3–4 mins per side for medium rare). Transfer steak to cutting board and slice across the grain.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10–15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan, then assemble tacos by layering steak and topping with chimichurri sauce.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Garnish with sliced red onions and cilantro, if desired.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Prepare red salsa by placing roasted vegetables, white onion, garlic, cilantro, stock and salt in blender. Blend until smooth. Set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat 2 teaspoon canola oil in medium non-stick skillet over medium-high heat; sauté onion and garlic until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes; stirring constantly.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Add zucchini and cook until just about softened, about 2 minutes. Then add the shrimp, cumin, and pepper, and grill until shrimp is red and cooked through, 4 to 5 minutes; stirring frequently. Remove from heat.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side in an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Assemble the tacos by spooning shrimp & zucchini mixture onto the tortillas. Top with red salsa.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a gallon size zip lock bag mix together all marinade ingredients. Add flank steak; refrigerate for at least 4 hours. One hour before grilling, remove steak from refrigerator and let set on counter. Meanwhile, heat grill to medium high heat. Remove steak from marinade and discard leftover marinade

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Place steak on grill and cook for 5 minutes on first side, turn over and cook an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until thermometer reaches at least 145 F. Slice steak across grain into thin slices; set aside, keep warm.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: In medium skillet over medium high heat add 2 tablespoons sesame oil, red pepper, carrot, and red onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp tender. Add spinach and 1 teaspoon water; cover, cook for 1 more minute or until spinach is wilted.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description:
To assemble tortilla:  Place about 2 ½ ounces steak down center of one flour tortilla, top with 2 tablespoons vegetable mixture, sprinkle with ½ teaspoon sesame seeds. Roll up or fold in half to serve.   

Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To grill chicken: Preheat oven to 350°F. Brush grilling skillet lightly with 1 teaspoon canola oil in medium high heat. Grill chicken breast on both sides about oil over medium high heat for about 5 minutes per side. Place in oven for about 10 to 14 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Prepare guacamole by placing the avocado in a bowl and mashing with a fork. Stir in tomato, chopped red onion, cilantro, lime juice, cilantro, salt, and pepper. Mix well. Set aside.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Heat 1 tablespoon canola oil in medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add red and green bell peppers, and sliced red onions, stirring constantly, until vegetables are tender, about 4 to 5 minutes. Season with salt.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Add chicken and cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until chicken is heated through.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: To assemble each burrito: lay warm tortilla out flat and spread 2 teaspoons of guacamole. Spoon 1/4 the amount of chicken down the middle of the tortilla. Wrap tightly. Serve warm with side of sour cream, if desired.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description:
To assemble tortilla: On one cooked flour tortilla spread 2 tablespoons peanut butter, sprinkle 2 tablespoons dried fruit, 1 tablespoon granola, and drizzle 1 teaspoon honey over all. Fold over or roll up to eat.  

Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To assemble tortilla pizza: On cooked side of one flour tortilla spread 2 tablespoons pizza sauce, 10 slices pepperoni, ¼ cup shredded cheese, and 1 tablespoon basil leaves.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description:
Place uncooked side of tortilla on medium high hot skillet. Cover; cook for 40 to 45 seconds. Remove from heat and cut into wedges.   

Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Place sweet potatoes in a one-quart saucepan with 2 cups of water. Bring the water to a boil, reduce the heat, and simmer until the vegetable is fork tender, about 2 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add onions, red and green bell peppers, stirring constantly until vegetables are tender, about 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: To assemble the burrito, place baby spinach each tortilla. Layer on sweet potatoes, onions, and bell peppers.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Top with avocado, onion, cheese and a pinch of salt & black pepper.

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: Roll up sides and serve warm.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In small bowl stir together all salmon mixture ingredients; mix well.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: To assemble tortilla:  On half of the cooked side of one flour tortilla sprinkle 2 tablespoons shredded cheese, top with about 1/3 cup salmon mixture, then sprinkle with another 2 tablespoons shredded cheese. Fold tortilla over salmon mixture.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description:
Place flour tortilla on medium high hot skillet. Cover; cook first side for 30 seconds; turn over tortilla and cook second side for additional 30 to 40 seconds. Remove from heat and cut in ½ to serve.  

Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add chorizo to skillet (no need to add oil), and cook until crisp, stirring occasionally; set aside in small bowl.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Add onion, garlic, and corn to same skillet where chorizo was cooked and sauté for 4 minutes in remaining chorizo fat. Season with cumin, salt, and pepper. Divide mixture evenly into 4 portions.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Assemble the tacos by filling the tortillas with chorizo, corn mixture, cheese, and avocado slices. Serve with Pico de Gallo salsa, if desired.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In small bowl stir together all tuna and egg mixture ingredients; mix well.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description:
To assemble tortilla:  Place about 1/3 cup tuna and egg mixture down center of corn tortilla; top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato. Roll up or fold in half to serve.   

Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To assemble tortilla: On cooked side of one flour tortilla spread 2 tablespoons almond butter, 1 tablespoon orange marmalade, and 1 tablespoon sliced almonds. Fold tortilla in half and place on medium high hot skillet.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description:
Cover; cook first uncooked side for 30 seconds; turn over tortilla and cook second side for additional 30 seconds. Remove from heat and cut in half.   

Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat butter in medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Stir in sugar, mixing constantly until syrup forms, 1 to 2 minutes. Add pear slices. Cook pears carefully in syrup stirring occasionally for about 1 minute.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Remove from heat and add cinnamon. Mix gently.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons cream cheese onto each tortilla, then add a layer of the pear mixture. Fold each tortilla in half and top with whipped cream.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Prepare tomatillo salsa by placing tomatillos, garlic, onion, jalapeño, cilantro, and vegetable broth in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. Transfer to saucepan and add 1 tablespoon olive oil. Cook until tomatillo sauce changes color to olive green about 5 to 6 minutes.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Preheat oven to 350°F.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Heat oil in medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add red onions and garlic and cook for 1 to 2 minutes until lightly brown. Add corn kernels, black beans and salt. Stir frequently until cooked evenly. Remove from heat.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Place corn/bean mixture evenly along center of each tortilla and fold. Place in oven safe platter seam side down. Top enchiladas with salsa and cotija cheese. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Serve with shredded napa cabbage and sour cream.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat oven to 350ºF. In small saucepan heat pork, beans, chili powder, cumin and garlic powder. Place chips in oven-proof 10-inch skillet or on baking sheet with sides. Top with pork mixture, cheese, jalapeño slices and bacon.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with toppings, if desired.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat oven to 350ºF. Brown chorizo in 10-inch oven-proof skillet. Remove cooked chorizo with slotted spoon; blot with paper towel.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Add shrimp to skillet. Cook shrimp in chorizo drippings until they are pink; remove from skillet and blot with paper towel. Drain fat from skillet; wipe with paper towel.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Place half of chips in skillet, top with half of chorizo, half of shrimp and half of cheese; repeat layers with remaining ingredients. Bake 5 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Meanwhile, in small bowl combine sour cream and lime juice; set aside. Sprinkle with tomato and cilantro, serve with sour cream mixture.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To make rice: place tomatoes, onions, garlic, and broth in blender. Blend until smooth.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In non-stick saucepan place tomato mixture, rice and 1 teaspoon olive oil. Mix slightly. Cook over medium high heat until it simmers. Cover, and lower heat. Cook for 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is soft. (Do not stir.) Turn heat off and leave covered until water has evaporated and rice is fully cooked.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Lightly coat bottom of a large non-stick pan with olive oil (about 2 teaspoons) and place over medium low heat.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Once hot, crack the eggs into the skillet leaving room between each to cook separately. Cook until the egg whites are set but the yolk is runny.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: To assemble tacos, place a layer of rice on each tortilla and top with an egg, avocado slices and black pepper. Repeat with remaining tortillas.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Pre-heat oven to 350° F.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Spread cream cheese into an ungreased shallow 1 quart baking dish. Layer with chicken, wing sauce, and ranch dressing. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese then blue cheese crumbles. Drizzle with additional wing sauce.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Bake uncovered for 20-25 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted. Serve warm with strips tortilla chips.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description:
To cook the chicken: 

In a large resealable plastic bag, combine all dry ingredients for chicken, add the oil, mix and add the sliced chicken breast. Seal and refrigerate for 15 minutes to an hour (begin queso while chicken is marinating). Remove chicken from refrigerator. 

Heat 1 tbsp. olive oil in a large non-stick skillet. Empty contents of bag into the hot skillet and squeeze lime juice to taste. Cook until chicken is cooked all the way through (about 6 minutes). 

Remove chicken from skillet and set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description:
To cook the queso: 

Heat the half-and-half over medium-high heat in a medium saucepan until simmering (do not boil, milk will foam around edges when ready). Once milk is ready, reduce heat to low and begin adding the cheese in batches while constantly stirring. 

Once cheese is melted, stir in all remaining ingredients other than garnishes. Stir to combine.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Chop chicken into 1 inch cubes and add to queso. Stir to combine. Pour queso into large serving bowl and enjoy.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat oven to 350ºF. Spray 8-inch glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Sauté onions 2 minutes or until crisp-tender. Add red bell pepper, chiles, chicken, sour cream and 1 ½ cup of the cheese. Cook and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Place crushed chips in sprayed pan. Top with chicken mixture, enchilada sauce and remaining ½ cup cheese. Bake 20 minutes or until mixture is hot and cheese is melted. Serve with toppings, if desired

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat canola oil over medium-high heat in a non-stick skillet. Sauté onion until tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and cook until tender and water has evaporated, about 5 to 6 minutes. Season with salt. Empty skillet into a bowl and set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat up the same non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Lightly brush one side of a tortilla with canola oil and lay brushed side down into the hot skillet. Spoon sautéed mixture and spread evenly. Top with a few rosemary leaves, mozzarella cheese and a slice of provolone cheese. Place second tortilla brushed side up on top.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Cook the quesadilla over medium heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese has melted and quesadilla is easy to turn. Gently turn the quesadilla over and cook 2 minutes more. Cook until quesadilla is light golden brown on both sides.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Repeat with remaining tortillas. Slice into quarters and serve warm.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Prepare green salsa by placing tomatillos, onion, jalapeño, cilantro, and salt in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. Transfer to saucepan and cook until tomatillo sauce changes color to olive green about 5 to 6 minutes.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat 1 tablespoon canola oil in medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add potatoes and red bell peppers, stirring constantly until potatoes are lightly browned and peppers are tender, about 4 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, and set aside.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side in an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Assemble flautas by spreading the mixture and shredded cheese evenly on center each tortilla, leaving a half inch border around the edges. Roll up the tortillas tightly. Heat 2 tablespoons canola oil on same skillet over medium high heat. Place flautas seam side down and allow to cook for 2 minutes. Carefully flip and continue cooking until evenly golden and crisp, about 4 to 5 minutes total.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Top flautas with warm green salsa and garnish with sour cream.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Fill a non-stick skillet with 1” water, and place over medium high heat. Place sliced sweet potato in hot water and cook until fork tender about 2 to 4 minutes. Set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: To make red salsa: place tomatoes, onion, garlic, serrano, cilantro, stock and salt in blender. Blend until smooth. Heat up 2 teaspoon canola oil in non-stick sauce pan over medium high heat. Add salsa, cook for about 4 to 6 minutes or until tomato changes to a deeper red color.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Heat longaniza (or chorizo) over medium high heat in medium non-stick skillet. Cook for about 2 to 4 minutes or until meat is cooked; stirring frequently. Set aside. In same skillet, add red onions and sauté until softened, about 1 minute; stirring constantly. Add sweet potatoes and cumin, and stir until sweet potatoes are cooked through.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side on an ungreased pan

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Assemble tacos by spooning sweet potato mixture onto the tortilla and topping with salsa roja and cotija cheese.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat canola oil in a medium non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add onion and garlic and sauté until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes; stirring frequently.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Add zucchini and yellow squash; sauté until tender, 3 to 4 minutes; stirring constantly. Remove from skillet and set aside.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10 to 15 seconds on each side in an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Assemble tacos by spreading warmed refried beans over each tortilla. Top with zucchini & yellow squash mix, and sour cream.

fields.name: For Roasted Peppers and Corn
fields.description:
1. On a baking sheet place two halves of the poblano pepper skin side up.

2. Add the corn in a single layer on the other side of the sheet.

3. Place under broiler for about 5 minutes or until corn is charred.

4. Remove corn from baking sheet and continue cooking peppers under broiler if needed, until skin is blistered and charred.

fields.name: For Guacamole
fields.description:
1. Scoop avocados into a large serving bowl with salt and pepper, cilantro, onion, and lime juice.

2. Mash with a fork or potato masher to desired consistency.

3. Stir in roasted poblano and corn, as well as the tomatoes.

4. Serve with Mission Organics Blue Corn Tortilla chips and enjoy!

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Mix all ingredients in small bowl; stir well.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Place salad mixture in serving bowl. Serve with blue chips.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat pan to medium-high heat.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Add minced shallots and butter, sauté till golden. Add ground beef and remaining seasonings. Brown beef and drain fat once fully cooked.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Add beer, and scrape the bottom of the pan to de-glaze.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Let simmer, stirring occasionally allowing flavors to meld, until reduced (about 2-3 minutes). Set aside.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: In a separate medium-sized sauce pan, heat milk till almost simmering (will just begin to boil at the edge).

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: Reduce heat to low, slowly stir in shredded cheese, mixing till you achieve a silky texture.

fields.name: Step 7
fields.description: Combine the queso with the cooked beef.

fields.name: Step 8
fields.description: Garnish with slices of avocado, sliced serranos, or chopped cilantro.

fields.name: Step 9
fields.description: Serve with Mission Organics Yellow Corn Tortilla Chips and enjoy.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Rub steak with 1 tsp. salt and pepper.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a large, heavy skillet over medium-high, heat 1 tbsp. oil. Cook steak, flipping once, until cooked to desired degree of doneness, 2-3 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: In same skillet heat remaining 1 tbsp. oil. Add bell pepper, asparagus, and mushrooms and ¼ tsp. salt and cook, stirring frequently, until tender, about 5 minutes.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: In a large, dry skillet over medium, heat tortillas 1 at a time, flipping once, until heated through and pliable. Transfer to a plate and warm remaining tortillas, stacking them on top of each other.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Thinly slice steak and serve with vegetables in tortillas. Top with avocado and salsa.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat grill. Season the chicken with the chili powder and ¾ tsp. salt. Grill the chicken, turning once, until the chicken is cooked through about 10 minutes.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Transfer the chicken to a plate to cool slightly. Cut chicken into cubes and top the tortillas with the chicken, mashed avocado and jalapeño slices.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Garnish with lime wedges and pomegranate.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large skillet heat oil over medium-high. Add onion and garlic and sauté until softened, 6-8 minutes. Stir in cumin, coriander, oregano, salt, and cayenne. Add turkey and cook, breaking up meat with a spoon, until cooked through and starting to brown, about 10 minutes.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a medium bowl whisk together lime juice, oil, Dijon, garlic, salt, and pepper. Toss dressing with kale, carrot, and green onion.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: In a large, dry skillet over medium, heat tortillas 1 at a time, flipping once, until heated through and pliable. Transfer to a plate and warm remaining tortillas, stacking them on top of each other.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Serve turkey and slaw with tortillas.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Shred the meat from the rotisserie chicken, yielding 2 cups. Season with Jamaican jerk seasoning and juice from ½ lime. Toss to coat. Reserve refrigerated.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Combine the tomatoes, pineapple, cilantro, jalapeño, red onion, a squeeze of lime juice, and salt together. Stir to combine. Reserve refrigerated.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: To serve, on each tortilla, place ¼ cup of the seasoned chicken, 2 tbsp. of the pineapple salsa, 1 tbsp. cabbage, and 1 tbsp. cheese.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Preheat oven to 400˚F.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Place chicken in a baking dish, coat with 1 teaspoon olive oil, ¾ teaspoon salt and paprika. Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until juices run clear, and chicken registers 165℉ on an instant-read thermometer. Transfer to cutting board, rest for 5 minutes and slice.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: In a medium bowl, combine yogurt, water, 2 teaspoons oil, vinegar, chives, dill, garlic powder, ¼ teaspoon salt and pepper until smooth.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Lay out tortillas on a clean work surface and layer each with lettuce, chicken, avocado and tomato. Top each with ranch then fold in one end and roll tightly to create wrap.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Prepare a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a small bowl, combine oil, paprika and salt. Rub salmon evenly with oil mixture.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Lightly grease the grill, transfer salmon to the hottest part of the grill, skin side down. Grill for 15 minutes or until salmon is opaque and flakes easily with a fork. Transfer to cutting board or plate and remove salmon skin.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: In a large bowl, beat to combine cream cheese and mayonnaise until light. Fold in onion, dill and capers.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Lay out tortillas on a clean work surface, spread with cream cheese mixture leaving a ½” border all the way around. Layer with lettuce leaves, salmon fillet and tomatoes. Fold in one end then roll tightly to create wrap.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a medium bowl whisk eggs with garlic, salt and pepper.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a large skillet over medium heat, warm oil. Add spinach and sauté until spinach begins to wilt. Pour in eggs and top with red peppers. Cook eggs, stirring frequently, until they begin to set, about 1 to 2 minutes. Sprinkle in feta cheese, stirring until eggs are completely set, about 1 to 2 minutes more.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Lay out tortillas on a clean work surface and top with eggs. Fold in one end then roll tightly to create wrap.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Cut apple in quarters, remove core and seeds, and thinly slice.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a large bowl whisk to combine vinegar, mustard, honey and oil. Add arugula, apples, and cranberries and toss evenly to coat.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Lay out tortillas on a clean work surface and layer each with turkey, cheese and apple-arugula salad. Fold in one end then roll tightly to create wrap.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Preheat oven to 425℉.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: On a large sheet pan toss together shrimp, bell pepper, onion, oil, chili powder, cumin, oregano, and salt. Roast until the shrimp are opaque and vegetables are just tender, about 10 minutes.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Serve vegetables and shrimp with tortillas. If desired, top with sour cream, cilantro, and/or green onion.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a medium bowl combine chicken, chile sauce, and cumin.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Lay tortillas on a work surface, and divide beans, chicken, and cheese between tortillas, placing all ingredients on ½ of each tortilla. Fold bare ½ of each tortilla over to cover fillings.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: In a large nonstick skillet heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium. Place 1 quesadilla in skillet and cook, flipping once, until golden brown on both sides, 2-3 minutes per side. Repeat with remaining oil and quesadillas. Cut quesadillas into wedges and serve warm.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Rub chicken with Cajun seasoning and, if seasoning is salt-free, salt.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a large skillet heat 1 tbsp. oil over medium-high. Add chicken and cook, turning once, until blackened on both sides and cooked through, 8-10 minutes. A thermometer inserted in the thickest part should read 170℉. Transfer chicken to a plate.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Add remaining 2 tbsp. oil to skillet, then add peppers and onion, and cook, stirring until softened, about 5 minutes.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Thinly slice chicken, and serve chicken and vegetables with tortillas. If desired, serve with parsley, green onion and/or hot sauce.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large nonstick skillet over medium, cook sausage, breaking up meat with a spoon, until browned, 8-10 minutes. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain and pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat from pan.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Add chiles to skillet and cook 1 minute. Stir in eggs and salt, reduce heat to medium-low, and cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are cooked through.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Working with 1 tortilla at a time, lay tortilla on work surface. Place 1 tablespoon beans in center of tortilla. Top with 1 tablespoon sausage, ¼ cup eggs, 1 tablespoon cheese, and 1 tablespoon salsa. Fold bottom of tortilla over fillings, fold in sides, then roll up. Place seam side down on work surface. Repeat with remaining tortillas and filling.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Wrap each burrito in plastic wrap, place in a zip-top bag, and freeze.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: To reheat, remove plastic wrap, place on a microwave-safe plate, and heat until completely thawed and warm, 1-2 minutes.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper. Heat a medium, heavy skillet over medium-high until hot. Cook steak, turning once, until browned on both sides but still pink inside, 2-3 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board and set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In same skillet, heat 1 tbsp. oil over medium. Add red and yellow bell peppers, onions, and cook, stirring until softened, 6-8 minutes. Add mushrooms and cook until softened, about 3 minutes more. Set aside.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Lay 4 tortillas on a flat surface, and divide steak and vegetables between them. Top with cheese and remaining tortillas.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: In a large nonstick skillet heat remaining 1 tbsp. oil over medium. Cook 1 quesadilla at a time, flipping once, until golden brown on both sides, about 3 minutes per side.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Rub steak with 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. In a large, heavy skillet over medium-high, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Cook steak, turning once, until cooked to desired degree of doneness, 2-3 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a nonstick skillet over medium, heat 1 tablespoon oil and chili powder. Add eggs and ½ teaspoon salt, reduce heat to medium-low, and cook, stirring occasionally until eggs are cooked through.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Thinly slice steak across the grain. Serve eggs and steak with tortillas, and top with cilantro.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In small bowl stir together sour cream and pesto sauce; set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat medium skillet over medium heat.  Add 2 tablespoons olive oil, potatoes, mushrooms, and onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are slightly browned (8 to 10 minutes); keep warm, set aside.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: In large skillet over medium heat add remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil.  Carefully break eggs, one at a time, into skillet.  Cook until bottom of eggs are set (3 to 4 minutes).   Carefully flip over each egg and continue cooking for 30 to 60 seconds.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: To assemble taco:  Down the center of one flour tortilla place ¼ of potato mixture, 1 cooked egg, 1 slice of bacon, and 1 tablespoon pesto sauce.  Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: On 1 flour tortilla, spread 1 tbsp. cream cheese and 1 tsp. raspberry jam.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Top with 1 sliced strawberry, about 8 blueberries and 4 raspberries. If desired, garnish with mini dollops of whipped cream.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Repeat with remaining flour tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: On one flour tortilla, spread 1 teaspoon of blue cheese dressing, grilled chicken, several thin slices of celery, and 1 teaspoon of crumbled blue cheese.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Drizzle with a few drops of Buffalo sauce.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Place the first seven ingredients in small skillet, over medium heat, to make the marinade.  Heat until mixture is hot (2 to 3 minutes); let cool.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Place flank steak in a large resealable plastic bag; add cooled marinade and cilantro leaves. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: One hour before grilling, take meat out of refrigerator and let sit on counter.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Heat grill to medium-high heat.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Remove steak from marinade and discard leftover marinade.

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: Cook steak for 5 minutes on first side, turn over and cook an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until thermometer reaches at least 145° F.

fields.name: Step 7
fields.description: Slice steak across grain into thin slices.

fields.name: Step 8
fields.description: Place several slices of steak in the center of one corn tortilla, add ¼ cup of shredded lettuce, 1 tbsp. shredded queso cheese, 1 tbsp. of salsa, and 1 slice of avocado. If desired, garnish with a dollop of sour cream and a slice of lime.  Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: On one flour tortilla, spread 1 teaspoon of Caesar dressing, top with 1 oz. of grilled chicken, 1 slice of bacon, 1 tablespoon of cheese, ¼ cup of lettuce, and 1 tablespoon of tomato.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In medium skillet over medium high heat, cook chorizo sausage, stirring to break meat into smaller pieces, until almost fully cooked (5 to 6 minutes).  Add chopped onion, peppers, and tomato.  Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are just tender (3 to 4 minutes).

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Remove meat mixture from pan.  In same skillet, add eggs, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring gently, until eggs are just cooked.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Using two stacked corn tortillas, add 3 tablespoons meat mixture, 2 tablespoons scrambled eggs and 1 avocado slice.  Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.   Easy and delicious.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: On one flour tortilla, spread 1 tablespoon of peanut butter. Top with several slices of banana, and drizzle with 1 teaspoon of honey.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Next, sprinkle with 1 tablespoon each of raisins and granola. If desired, sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of mini chocolate chips.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a crock pot, place water then pork roast.  Sprinkle roast with pork seasoning and paprika. Cover; set temperature to HIGH and cook for 6 hours or until pork is tender enough to shred with a fork.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Reserve 1 cup of drippings.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: To shred pork: remove pork from crock pot and place on cutting board.  Remove any fat pieces, then pull apart pork into small pieces and place in a large bowl; add reserved drippings and mix well.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, stir together cabbage and coleslaw dressing; mix well.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Down the center of one corn tortilla, place ¼ cup meat then top with 2 tablespoons coleslaw.  Repeat with remaining tortillas and coleslaw.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a small saucepan mix together pineapple juice, lime juice, sugar, soy sauce, and pepper. Bring to a boil and cook until syrupy, 4-6 minutes.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Prepare a hot grill fire or heat a grill pan over medium-high. Rub pork chops and onion with oil and sprinkle with salt. Place pork, onions, and pineapple on grill or grill pan and cook, turning, until pork is cooked to desired degree of doneness, 6-8 minutes per side depending on thickness. Internal temperature should be at least 145℉.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: During last 1-2 minutes of cooking, baste chops with soy mixture, turning frequently, until glazed and well-browned. Grill onion and pineapple until charred and softened.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: To serve, thinly slice pork chops and toss pork with any remaining glaze, chop pineapple, and separate onion into rings. Serve pork, pineapple, and onion on 2 stacked tortillas per taco, and top with green onion and chile.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large skillet heat oil over medium-high. Add chicken and salt and cook. Stir until cooked through, about 5 minutes.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a medium saucepan over medium-low whisk together peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, ginger, garlic, red pepper flakes, and ½ of cup water. Keep warm, whisking occasionally.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Serve chicken with 2 stacked tortillas per taco. Top with cabbage, pepper, carrot, cilantro, and green onion. Drizzle tacos with peanut sauce.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a medium bowl stir together olives, peppers, vinegar, garlic, and oregano.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Lay tortillas on a work surface. Spread a thin layer of olive mixture over each tortilla, then divide salami, ham, and provolone between tortillas. Fold tortillas in half.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Serve at room temperature or cold with Dijon mustard.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large bowl, mix tuna, scallions, sesame seeds, soy sauce, toasted sesame oil, honey and crushed red pepper.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Season with a small pinch of kosher salt and gently fold to combine. Taste and adjust with more soy sauce, sesame oil, honey, or crushed red pepper as desired. Let mixture marinate for five minutes at room temperature.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10-15 seconds on each side in an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Add tuna mixture to each tortilla and roll up to

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To make pickled cucumber salad: Combine sliced cucumbers with  rice vinegar, water, black sesame seeds and scallions. Let sit for an hour or more depending on desired pickling.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a large bowl, marinate chicken in ponzu for at least 30 minutes.  If marinating overnight, cover bowl and place in fridge.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Preheat oven to 375˚ F degrees.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Place marinated chicken in oven safe/cast iron skillet. Roast uncovered for about 30 minutes or until chicken is evenly browned. Tear/dice chicken to bite sized pieces.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: To make garlic ponzu sauce: in a small sauce pan, heat sesame oil and cook garlic until slightly brown. Add water carefully, ponzu sauce, soy sauce and brown sugar. Stir constantly until sugar dissolves, then set aside to cool slightly.

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: Assemble taco with chicken and a generous amount of garlic ponzu sauce. Add pickled cucumber salad and top with pea shoots. Serve with additional sauce if desired.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a medium sized mixing bowl, combine rice vinegar, water,  and slivered red onions to quick pickle. Let sit for an hour or more depending on desired pickling.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In a small sauce pan, whisk together coconut milk and red curry paste, bring to boil. Stir in tofu and allow to simmer for a few minutes. Turn off stove, set pan aside away from heat.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Assemble taco with tofu and red curry. Top with pickled red onion, crispy rice noodles, bean sprouts and sliced pepperoncini.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Garnish with chopped cilantro and lime wedges.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large mixing bowl, combine ground lamb, crumbled feta and mint. Using hands, roll/shape into half dollar-sized meatballs.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat about 1/2 inch of oil in frying pan. Without over-crowding the pan, fry meatballs about 1 minute per side, or until golden brown on all sides. Place on paper towel-lined plate.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: While meatballs are resting, make yogurt sauce by combining yogurt, garlic, dill and mint.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Assemble tacos by spreading yogurt sauce, adding meatballs,  sliced cucumbers, additional feta, and chopped parsley.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large bowl, mix minced jalapeño, corn, black beans, salt, pepper and ground cumin.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10-15 seconds on each side in an ungreased pan, making them more pliable and ready for filling. Place 2 teaspoons of filling, ½ teaspoon guacamole and a sprinkle of shredded cheese in the center of the flour tortilla.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Fold over tortilla and moisten edges with egg wash; press to seal with fork. Repeat with remaining tortillas and filling.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Place all empanadas in a baking tray coated with cooking spray. Lightly brush empanadas with additional egg wash for shine. Bake at 425°F for 4-5 on each side until golden brown.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Let cream cheese sit and bring to room temp.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Meanwhile, soak the cranberries in warm water for 20-30 minutes until they begin to plump up.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Remove skins from roasted garlic and mash into a fine paste.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Fold cranberries and roasted garlic into the cream cheese.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve in a bowl with Mission Thin & Crispy Tortilla Chips.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large bowl, whisk together yogurt, oil, curry powder, garlic, ginger, paprika, turmeric, and salt. Add shrimp, toss to coat, cover and refrigerate for 4-6 hours.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Preheat broiler and Line a baking sheet with foil.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Remove shrimp from marinade, allowing excess to drip off, and place on baking sheet. Bake until cooked through and starting to brown, 8 minutes.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Place shrimp on tortillas and top with mango and cilantro. If desired, served with lime wedges and yogurt.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a large bowl mix goat cheese, honey, salt and then refrigerate 1-2 hours. Chop nuts and parsley and combine.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Warm up your cranberry sauce and spread it on a cheese tray or serving platter.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Roll chilled goat cheese into a ball and then cover with nut mixture and dried cranberries.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Set the goat cheese ball over the cranberry sauce and sprinkle any leftover nuts on the platter. Serve with Mission Strips Tortilla Chips.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Put the pork belly in a roasting pan that holds it snugly, fat side up. Combine 1/4 cup salt and 1/4 cup sugar in a small bowl and rub all over the pork. Cover and marinate in refrigerator for at least 6 hours, but no more than 24 hours.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: When ready to cook: Preheat oven to 450°F. Pour out any accumulated liquid at the bottom of the roasting pan. Place pan with pork belly in the oven. Cook for 30 minutes, basting it with the rendered fat halfway through, until it’s golden brown.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Turn the oven temperature down to 250°F and cook until the pork is tender, another 2 hours, basting and turning as needed. Transfer the pork to a plate, decant the fat and the meat juices from the pan and reserve it for the tacos. Allow the pork to cool slightly.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: When cool enough to handle, wrap the pork in plastic wrap or aluminum foil refrigerate for at least one hour until it’s thoroughly chilled and firm. When completely chilled, cut the pork belly into 1/2-inch-slices about 2 inches long.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Combine the cucumbers with white vinegar, remaining sugar and salt in a small mixing bowl and toss to coat. Let sit for an hour. Use right away or refrigerate for up to 4 hours.

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: When ready to serve, warm pork in a pan over medium heat for a minute or two, until soft and heated through.

fields.name: Step 7
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10-15 seconds on each side in an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 8
fields.description: On each tortilla, layer pork belly slices, cucumbers, red onions, and cilantro. Add Sriracha to taste and serve.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Pre-heat oven to 350ºF. Spread cream cheese into an ungreased shallow 1 quart baking dish.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Layer with chicken, celery, wing sauce, and ranch dressing. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese then blue cheese crumbles. Drizzle with additional wing sauce.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Bake uncovered for 20-25 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Serve in a bowl with Mission Strips Tortilla Chips. Add red and green peppers around bowl for garnish.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To prepare salsa: Combine mango (or pineapple), cilantro, red onion and half of a squeezed lime. Set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In medium sized bowl toss together melted butter, raw shrimp, and Jamaican jerk seasoning

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Preheat skillet to medium high and add oil. Fry shrimp in preheated pan for about 2 minutes on each side, or until golden crusted.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Assemble tacos by layering shrimp, cabbage and mango salsa.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Serve with lime wedges.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In large saucepan, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add onion, garlic and bell peppers; sauté 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Stir in jalapeño peppers, chiles, cumin and oregano; cook and stir an additional 2 minutes.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Reduce heat to low, stir in beans and chicken broth. Cook 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in 1 cup of the cheese and ¼ cup of the sour cream until melted.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Serve chili with crushed chips, remaining ½ cup cheese, remaining ¼ cup sour cream and chopped cilantro.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Make falafel according to package instructions, set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: To make parsley salad (tabbouleh) combine chopped parsley, diced tomatoes, diced onion, lemon juice, and salt and pepper to taste.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Assemble tacos by spreading hummus, then layering falafel, tabbouleh and julienned cucumbers.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Serve with tzatziki sauce.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In large skillet brown ground beef with onion until beef is no longer pink; drain fat and return to skillet. Add taco seasoning and water; cook according to package directions.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Remove taco meat from heat and stir in coleslaw mixture. Divide meat mixture evenly into 4 bowls.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description:
Top each bowl with ¼ cup lettuce, 1 tablespoon salsa, ¼ cup tortilla chips, 2 tablespoons cheddar cheese, 1 tablespoon sour cream and 1 tablespoon guacamole. 

Serve immediately.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Cut the chicken into bite sized pieces. Marinate with 1 tablespoon of masala paste and the yogurt for at least 30 minutes (or up to 4 hours) in the refrigerator.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Once marinating is complete, melt butter in a large, deep skillet over medium high heat and add the remaining masala paste. Allow to fry for 1 minute, then add onion, garlic and ginger.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Add the chicken/yogurt mixture and sauté until the chicken is nearly cooked.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Lastly, add the tomato puree and cream/coconut milk and allow to simmer for 15 minutes or until sauce thickens and chicken is thoroughly cooked. Season with salt, as desired.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10-15 seconds on each side in an ungreased pan. On each tortilla, lay a small bed of rice and top with chicken tikka masala mixture. Sprinkle with cilantro for garnish, if desired.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In medium bowl combine shredded rotisserie chicken and buffalo hot sauce; set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In large bowl combine remaining ingredients.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description:
Add sauce coated chicken to lettuce mixture; gently toss to combine. 

Serve immediately.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: To make mojo sauce: Heat up 2 tbsp. olive oil in a small saucepan over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until softened. Stir in the lime/orange juice, cilantro, and salt. Set aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Prepare grill to medium high heat. Brush fillets thoroughly with coconut oil and season generously with salt and pepper.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Lay fish on the grill, rounded-side down, and leave until you can lift the fish without sticking and there are distinct grill marks, about 5 minutes. (Test it by gently lifting a corner—if it sticks, cook it a bit longer and try again). Carefully turn the fish over and cook until firm to the touch, about another 5 minutes. Cut into smaller chunks when cooled.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Warm tortillas for 10-15 seconds on each side in an ungreased pan.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Place a bed of greens on each tortilla, top with grilled fish and a generous serving of the mojo sauce. Garnish with cilantro sprigs.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In large saucepan heat oil. Add onion, chiles, garlic, carrots and celery. Cook 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Add beans, tomatoes and broth; simmer 15 minutes.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description:
Stir in remaining ingredients. 

Serve soup with toppings, if desired.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In medium skillet brown chorizo until no longer pink; drain fat and blot with paper towel. Set cooked chorizo aside.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: In medium saucepan melt butter. Add onion and cook 2 minutes.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Whisk in flour; cook 1 minute and whisk in milk. Stir in cheeses until melted.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Stir in chiles, peppers and reserved cooked chorizo. Transfer cheese dip to serving dish. Serve with Mission Thin & Crispy Tortilla Chips.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Heat oven to 350ºF. In medium bowl combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream, cheese, dips mix and jalapeños.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Spread mixture in shallow baking dish. Bake 15 minutes or until hot.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Sprinkle with green onion. Serve with Mission Thin & Crispy Tortilla Chips.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Add chopped red pepper to blender and blend until the pepper becomes a paste.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description:
In a large bowl, add all remaining ingredients (other than chips). Pour pepper paste over and mix until thoroughly combined.

For best results, chill for up to 1 hour before serving.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: If you want to give this sweet-and-spicy salsa a smokier flavor, cut the red pepper in half, deseed, place the pepper skin side up on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, and place into a 450ºF degree oven for 25 minutes or until the skins are wrinkled and lightly charred.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Add roasted pepper to blender and continue the remaining steps.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile, broil poblano chile 8 minutes or until skin is blistered and blackening; turning twice.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Remove pepper from oven and wrap in clean dish towel 5 minutes to steam. Remove stem and seeds of pepper and chop; set aside.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Heat oven to 350°F. In medium saucepan melt butter. Add onion and cook 2 minutes.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Whisk in flour and dry mustard; cook 1 minute and whisk in milk. Stir in Monterey Jack cheese and 2 cups of the cheddar cheese until melted.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: When melted, cook and stir 3 minutes or until sauce is thickened. Add cheese sauce to cooked pasta.

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: Transfer mixture to sprayed 9×13 glass baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheddar cheese and tortilla chips.

fields.name: Step 7
fields.description: Bake 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and chips are golden brown. Garnish with cilantro, if desired.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In blender combine tomatoes, chiles, cumin, cinnamon and salt; blend until smooth.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Heat oil over medium heat in large skillet with sides. Cook onion and garlic 2 minutes or until onion is tender. Add tomato mixture and chicken broth; bring to a boil.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: Reduce heat, simmer 10 minutes or until slightly thickened. Add tortilla chips, making sure each chip is coated in tomato sauce.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description:
Top with cheese, chicken, remaining tablespoon onion, sour cream and cilantro. 

Serve immediately.

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a food processor or blender, combine tomatillos, onion, chipotles, cilantro, garlic, salt, and sugar. Coarsely puree, leaving the mixture slightly chunky.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Transfer to a bowl and stir in enough water to loosen the mixture to a salsa-like consistency (up to 2 tbsp). Taste and add salt as needed. Serve with Mission Strips Tortilla Chips and enjoy!

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: Preheat oven to 375℉. In a medium bowl beat together cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, and garlic powder until smooth.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Stir in 1 cup Cheddar, 1 cup Pepper Jack, and jalapeños. Scrape mixture into a 3-cup baking dish and set aside.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: In a skillet over medium heat, cook bacon, turning once or twice, until browned and crisp, 8-10 minutes. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: dd panko to bacon fat in skillet and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Transfer panko to a medium bowl.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Crumble bacon and stir into panko along with remaining ¼ cup Cheddar and ¼ cup pepper Jack.

fields.name: Step 6
fields.description: prinkle panko mixture on top of dip. Bake until bubbly and browned, about 15 minutes. Serve on top of Mission Rounds Tortilla Chips and enjoy!

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: In a food processor combine sour cream, cream cheese, peppers, garlic, paprika, salt, and cayenne. Process or blend until very smooth.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: Transfer to a bowl and top with basil. Serve with Mission Strips Tortilla Chips and enjoy!

fields.name: Step 1
fields.description: First, choose an oven broiler or an outdoor barbecue grill for cooking.

fields.name: Step 2
fields.description: For broiler: arrange tomatoes, onion, garlic, and jalapeños on a baking sheet lined with foil. Broil close to the heat, turning vegetables occasionally until charred, 12-15 minutes. You may need to remove garlic from oven before other vegetables are finished cooking.

fields.name: Step 3
fields.description: For grill: lightly brush tomatoes, onion, and jalapeños with oil. Place jalapeños and garlic in a grill basket, and place tomatoes and onion wedges directly on grill grate. Grill, turning frequently until vegetables are charred, about 10 minutes.

fields.name: Step 4
fields.description: Once cooked, transfer tomatoes, onion, peeled garlic and jalapeños to a blender or food processor. For a milder salsa, remove seeds from jalapeños.

fields.name: Step 5
fields.description: Add lime juice, cumin, coriander, oregano, and salt to your blender or food processor and pulse until vegetables are finely ground.

fields.name: Step 6
